parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective drive shaft design can cause excessive vibration throughout the chassis, leading to potential handling failure, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Excessive vibration throughout the chassis
difficulty in handling the vehicle
possibility of drive shaft failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear axle being too light for the weight of the coach and overhang can cause handling issues, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Handling issues
loss of control
excessive wear on rear axle components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheating of the right front brake can lead to a loss of braking performance, increasing the stopping distance and risk of accidents.
symptoms: Burning odor from the right front brake area
excessive heat emanating from the right front wheel
grinding or scraping noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate headlight performance can reduce visibility, making it difficult for drivers to see the road ahead, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Bright and low beam headlights appear to be the same intensity
headlights are dim
headlights do not provide sufficient illumination
difficulty seeing the road ahead at night or in low-light conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a burning smell, which can lead to a fire, and potentially result in a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Burning smell from the ignition switch
smoke coming from the ignition switch
sparks or arcing from the ignition switch
difficulty turning the key
the key gets stuck in the ignition switch
the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high idling problem can cause the engine to rev excessively, leading to increased fuel consumption, wear and tear on engine components, and potential overheating issues, which can affect vehicle performance and safety.
symptoms: The engine idles at an excessively high RPM
the engine revs excessively when the vehicle is stationary
the engine makes a loud or unusual noise when idling
the vehicle's temperature gauge rises excessively when idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty idle air control valve can cause the engine to idle erratically, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential stalling, which can affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: The engine idles rough or erratically
the engine stalls frequently
the engine has difficulty starting
the "check engine" light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle body issues can cause the engine to idle poorly, leading to decreased fuel efficiency, poor engine performance, and potential stalling, which can affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: The engine idles rough or erratically
the engine stalls frequently
the engine has difficulty starting
the "check engine" light is illuminated
the throttle body is clogged or dirty.
